### direct democracy ###

types
    legislative referred state statute
        state legislatures vote to have citizens vote on new law
        not in texas
    initiated state statute
        initiated and enacted by voters
        not in texas
    veto referendum (popular referendum)
        one state or local law is enacted
            citizens can petition law to be on ballot to veto or ratify it

        not in texas
    statute affirmation
        voters affirm statute to prevent legislature from ever amending it
    recall elections
        voters can recall some or all elected officials
    legislatively referred constitutional amendment
        deleware doesnt allow this
    initiated constitutional amendment
        not in texas